Ground Rules: When to Use What
The Decision Framework
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    START HERE                            │
│              What is your problem?                       │
└─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────┘
                      │
          ┌───────────▼────────────┐
          │  Is the task well-     │
          │  defined with fixed    │──── YES ──→  MICROSERVICE
          │  input/output?         │              (just do the job)
          └───────────┬────────────┘
                      │ NO
          ┌───────────▼────────────┐
          │  Does it require       │
          │  reasoning, judgment,  │──── YES ──→  AGENT
          │  or decision-making?   │              (think then act)
          └───────────┬────────────┘
                      │ NO
          ┌───────────▼────────────┐
          │  Does it need multi-   │
          │  step coordination     │──── YES ──→  AGENTIC SYSTEM
          │  across many tools?    │              (multiple agents
          └───────────┬────────────┘               working together)
                      │ NO
          ┌───────────▼────────────┐
          │  Is it a simple        │
          │  request/response?     │──── YES ──→  PLAIN API
          └────────────────────────┘



Side-by-Side Comparison
MICROSERVICE                 AGENT                    AGENTIC SYSTEM
 ────────────                 ─────                    ──────────────

 ┌──────────┐           ┌──────────────┐          ┌──────────────────┐
 │  INPUT   │           │    GOAL      │          │   BIG GOAL       │
 └────┬─────┘           └──────┬───────┘          └───────┬──────────┘
      │                        │                          │
      ▼                        ▼                          ▼
 ┌──────────┐           ┌──────────────┐          ┌──────────────────┐
 │  Fixed   │           │   Thinks &   │          │  Planner Agent   │
 │  Logic   │           │   Plans      │          │  breaks it down  │
 └────┬─────┘           └──────┬───────┘          └───────┬──────────┘
      │                        │                          │
      ▼                        ▼                    ┌─────┼──────┐
 ┌──────────┐           ┌──────────────┐           ▼     ▼      ▼
 │  OUTPUT  │           │  Uses Tools  │       ┌──────┐┌────┐┌──────┐
 └──────────┘           └──────┬───────┘       │Agent ││Agt ││Agent │
                               │               │  A   ││ B  ││  C   │
                               ▼               └──┬───┘└──┬─┘└──┬───┘
                        ┌──────────────┐          │       │     │
                        │  Evaluates   │          ▼       ▼     ▼
                        │  "Good       │       ┌──────────────────┐
                        │   enough?"   │       │  Results merge   │
                        └──────┬───────┘       └────────┬─────────┘
                          NO╱    ╲YES                   │
                          ╱       ╲                     ▼
                     loops      ┌──────┐         ┌──────────────┐
                     back       │RESULT│         │ FINAL RESULT │
                                └──────┘         └──────────────┘

 Predictable            Adaptive               Collaborative
 Fast                   Smart                  Orchestrated
 One job                One goal               Many goals



The Cheat Sheet: 5 Ground Rules
╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║                                                                      ║
║   RULE 1: "CAN YOU WRITE AN IF-ELSE FOR IT?"                        ║
║   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐                        ║
║   │  YES → Microservice                     │                        ║
║   │  NO  → Agent                            │                        ║
║   └─────────────────────────────────────────┘                        ║
║                                                                      ║
║   Example:                                                           ║
║   • "Convert PDF to text"       → if/else works → MICROSERVICE      ║
║   • "Summarize this PDF and                                          ║
║     decide what to do with it"  → needs judgment → AGENT             ║
║                                                                      ║
╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣
║                                                                      ║
║   RULE 2: "HOW MANY STEPS ARE UNKNOWN UPFRONT?"                     ║
║   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐                        ║
║   │  Steps known     → Microservice         │                        ║
║   │  Steps unknown   → Agent                │                        ║
║   │  Many unknown    → Agentic System       │                        ║
║   └─────────────────────────────────────────┘                        ║
║                                                                      ║
║   ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌────────────────────┐        ║
║   │ Step1→Step2  │  │ Step1→ ???   │  │ ???→ ???→ ???→ ???  │        ║
║   │  →Step3→Done │  │  → ??? →Done │  │  → ???→ ??? →Done  │        ║
║   │ MICROSERVICE │  │    AGENT     │  │  AGENTIC SYSTEM    │        ║
║   └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └────────────────────┘        ║
║                                                                      ║
╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣
║                                                                      ║
║   RULE 3: "DOES IT NEED TO RECOVER FROM FAILURE?"                    ║
║   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐                        ║
║   │  Fails → return error   → Microservice  │                        ║
║   │  Fails → try another    → Agent         │                        ║
║   │          way                             │                        ║
║   └─────────────────────────────────────────┘                        ║
║                                                                      ║
║   Microservice:          Agent:                                      ║
║   "File not found"       "File not found...                         ║
║    → Error 404            let me search elsewhere                    ║
║                           → found it on backup                       ║
║                           → done!"                                   ║
║                                                                      ║
╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣
║                                                                      ║
║   RULE 4: "WHO DECIDES WHAT TO DO NEXT?"                             ║
║   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐                        ║
║   │  Developer writes the flow → Microservice│                       ║
║   │  AI decides at runtime     → Agent       │                       ║
║   └─────────────────────────────────────────┘                        ║
║                                                                      ║
║   Microservice: Developer pre-programs every path                    ║
║   Agent:        LLM chooses the next action dynamically              ║
║                                                                      ║
╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣
║                                                                      ║
║   RULE 5: "WHAT IS THE COST OF BEING WRONG?"                        ║
║   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐                        ║
║   │  High risk (payments, medical)           │                       ║
║   │    → Microservice (deterministic)        │                       ║
║   │                                          │                       ║
║   │  Low risk (drafts, research, search)     │                       ║
║   │    → Agent (creative, flexible)          │                       ║
║   │                                          │                       ║
║   │  Mixed → Agent + human approval gate     │                       ║
║   └─────────────────────────────────────────┘                        ║
║                                                                      ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝




How Is an Agentic System Configured?
This is where the rules and config come in:
╔═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║               ANATOMY OF AN AGENT CONFIG                         ║
╠═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣
║                                                                   ║
║  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐     ║
║  │                                                         │     ║
║  │  AGENT CONFIG = 5 THINGS                                │     ║
║  │                                                         │     ║
║  │  1. SYSTEM PROMPT     → "You are a customer support     │     ║
║  │     (personality         agent. Be polite. Always       │     ║
║  │      & rules)            verify the order number."      │     ║
║  │                                                         │     ║
║  │  2. TOOLS             → [search_orders, send_email,     │     ║
║  │     (what it CAN do)     check_inventory, issue_refund] │     ║
║  │                                                         │     ║
║  │  3. GUARDRAILS        → "Never refund > $500 without    │     ║
║  │     (what it CAN'T do)   human approval"                │     ║
║  │                                                         │     ║
║  │  4. MEMORY/CONTEXT    → conversation history, user      │     ║
║  │     (what it knows)      profile, past interactions     │     ║
║  │                                                         │     ║
║  │  5. ORCHESTRATION     → how agents hand off to each     │     ║
║  │     (how agents          other, who is the "boss"       │     ║
║  │      work together)                                     │     ║
║  │                                                         │     ║
║  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘     ║
║                                                                   ║
╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝


How the Loop Actually Works
 THE AGENTIC LOOP (this is what makes it "agentic")
  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────

       ┌──────────────────┐
       │   Receive GOAL   │ ← "Handle this customer complaint"
       └────────┬─────────┘
                │
       ┌────────▼─────────┐
       │   THINK          │ ← LLM reasons: "I need to look up
       │   (LLM call)     │    their order first"
       └────────┬─────────┘
                │
       ┌────────▼─────────┐
       │   ACT            │ ← Calls tool: search_orders("12345")
       │   (tool call)    │
       └────────┬─────────┘
                │
       ┌────────▼─────────┐
       │   OBSERVE        │ ← Gets result: "Order shipped late"
       │   (read result)  │
       └────────┬─────────┘
                │
       ┌────────▼─────────┐     ┌─────────────────────┐
       │   EVALUATE       │     │                     │
       │   "Am I done?"   ├─NO──▶  Loop back to THINK │
       │                  │     │                     │
       └────────┬─────────┘     └─────────────────────┘
                │ YES
       ┌────────▼─────────┐
       │   RESPOND        │ ← "I've issued a 15% discount 
       │                  │    and emailed the customer"
       └──────────────────┘

  THIS LOOP IS THE HEART OF "AGENTIC"
  Without it, you just have an LLM answering questions.





The Core Paradigm Shift
╔═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║                                                               ║
║  TRADITIONAL PROGRAMMING                                      ║
║  "HOW to do it" (Procedural/Imperative)                      ║
║                                                               ║
║  You write:  STEP 1 → STEP 2 → STEP 3                        ║
║                                                               ║
║  ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────      ║
║                                                               ║
║  AGENTIC PROGRAMMING                                          ║
║  "WHAT to achieve" (Declarative/Goal-oriented)               ║
║                                                               ║
║  You write:  GOAL + CONSTRAINTS + TOOLS                       ║
║              LLM figures out: STEP ? → STEP ? → STEP ?        ║
║                                                               ║
╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

The 5 Fundamental Shifts
SHIFT 1: From "Instructions" to "Outcomes"
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  OLD MINDSET: Tell the computer HOW                         │
│  ────────────────────────────────────                        │
│  "Do step A, then B, then C"                                │
│                                                             │
│  NEW MINDSET: Tell the AI WHAT                              │
│  ────────────────────────────────                            │
│  "Achieve this outcome, here are your tools and limits"     │
│                                                             │
└───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────




### **SHIFT 2: From "Control Flow" to "Capability Definition"**
```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  OLD MINDSET: Design the flowchart                          │
│  ────────────────────────────────────                        │
│  Draw every if-else branch                                  │
│  Map every exception path                                   │
│                                                             │
│  NEW MINDSET: Define the playing field                      │
│  ────────────────────────────────                            │
│  What CAN it do? (tools)                                    │
│  What MUST it follow? (rules)                               │
│  What MUST it achieve? (goal)                               │
│  LLM figures out the path                                   │
│                                                             │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘


